From the Infowars web site ::

 
On the Tuesday edition of the show, Alex talks about the success of a second march on the Texas capitol as lawmakers sell-out on a TSA anti-groping bill. 

Alex talks with Texas congressman Ron Paul about the TSA and the unconstitutional war on Libya. 

He also talks with retired U.S. Air Force Lt. Col. Craig Roberts, who served 12 years working as the Ground Liaison Officer in the Intelligence Section of the 138th Tactical Fighter Group. 

Author, researcher, and radio show host Webster Tarpley files a report [hour 4 overdrive] from Tripoli, Libya, where he is witnessing the U.S. and NATO bombardment of that country.
